The standard pattern for "building up" strings in C code is otherwise to use growarray, i e
```
garray_T ga;
ga_init(&ga, (int)sizeof(char *), 10);

// in a loop or something
snprintf((char *)IObuff, IOSIZE, "%d", idx);
ga_concat(&ga, IObuff);

ga_append(&ga, ';');
```

perhaps we should have `ga_printf` directly also, so it is easier to use.

