comment_regular_data.body:
@leonerd For a weird sequence like `\033[z`, the CSI fallback handler gets `argcount = 1`. Shouldn't it be 0?

Building the actual CSI sequence from the arguments of the fallback handler is rather complicated. Would it be possible to provide the whole sequence as another argument? So it can easily be forwarded to an outer term?

Then we could simply do this in Nvim:

```c
static VTermParserCallbacks vterm_parser_callbacks = {
  .csi = term_unhandled_csi,
};

static int term_unhandled_csi(const char *rawcmd, const char *leader,
                              const long args[], int argcount,
                              const char *intermed, char command, void *user)
{
  ui_call_term_unhandled(STATIC_CSTR_AS_STRING(rawcmd));
  return 1;
}
